Exaggerate: The claim exaggerates by presenting fake images of The Washington Times newspaper with the headline "President Gore" after the 2000 election.
Lack enough support: The claim lacks enough support as there is no evidence or factual basis for the images presented.
Contradict fact: The claim contradicts the fact that The Washington Times did not publish a headline declaring Al Gore as the winner of the 2000 election.
Problematic assumption: The claim assumes that the fake images presented by Tim Murtaugh are evidence of media bias in the 2020 election.
Exist alternative explanation: There is an alternative explanation for the fake images, which suggests they were created as a fictional version of the 2000 election on an "alternative history" online forum.
